div.p:
That when King Henry the VIII. Granted the Disposition of Felons Goods de se to his Almoner, and without revoking the same, Granted divers Felons Goods to one Hales;
                  Cooks Rep. Alton Woods Case.
                   and the Almoner disputed the Right, because the Stat. 6 Hen. 8. cap. 15. Saith, All after Grants shall be void, if the first be not recited and revoked: Yet it was Adjudged, That the Kings Grant to Hales was good against the Almoner, because he was only a Minister in Trust for the King: And Great Ministers are no other, neither have they such express Grants of the Disposition of Inferior Offices, as the Almoner had of Felons Goods.
